Q. Write a simple calculater program by using Apex call , where we can create 4 function for performing add , sub , mul and div.
public class CalculatorClass {
    public static void add(){
        Integer a = 10, b = 20;
        Integer sum = a+b;
        system.debug('Addition of a and b is ' + sum);
    }
    public static void subb(){
        Integer a = 50, b = 20;
        Integer sub = a-b;
        system.debug('sub of a & b is ' + sub);
    }
    public static void multiplication(){
        Integer a = 5 , b = 2;
        Integer mul = a*b;
        system.debug('multiplication of a and b is ' + mul);
    }
    public static void division(){
        Integer a = 100 , b = 5;
        Integer div = a/b;
        system.debug('div of a and b is ' + div);
    }
}



In debug we need to mention.
CalculatorClass.add();
CalculatorClass.subb();
CalculatorClass.multiplication();
CalculatorClass.multiplication();
